<item>
            <title>[OPENJPA-1308] shouldn&apos;t always use CAST with UPPER and LOWER for DB2</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OPENJPA-1308</link>
                <project id="12310351" key="OPENJPA">OpenJPA</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Using DB2, when a user uses the UPPER or LOWER function, the field is automatically CAST to a varchar.  It would be nice if OpenJPA were a little smarter and only used CAST when necessary.  Using the CAST causes any indexes not to be used so performance won&apos;t be what it should.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I saw some other DB2 functions that also are always CAST, so we may need to improve these also.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>DB2</environment>
